{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Follow-up — retracting the earlier \"declined over-specification.\" Per reviewer direction, the poll interval and staleness threshold are design-time judgement calls that must be fixed here (a less-capable implementation agent should not have to invent them). Now pinned, consistently across S2/S4/S5:\n\n- **Bot poll interval = 15 s** (S2, the loop cadence): picks up a freshly-`Autosubmit`'d change within ~15 s while staying gentle on the Gerrit REST API; intentionally distinct from `land`'s 30 s client-side poll (S4).\n- **Heartbeat cadence = every poll (≤ 15 s)** (S5 AC5), tied to S2's 15 s loop.\n- **`lander_down` staleness threshold = 90 s** (S4) = 6× the 15 s poll: absorbs a few consecutive slow iterations / a transient Gerrit hiccup without a false positive, yet fires ~20× sooner than the 30-min `--wait` timeout.\n- **AC6 time-to-land histogram buckets = 30 s, 1 m, 2 m, 5 m, 10 m, 20 m, 30 m, 1 h** (S5): spans a green fast-forward landing (~1–2 min CI re-run) through a contended `N=5` re-drive, so p50/p90/p99 are readable."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783784554130325001,"uuid":"7f07a23e-c3dd-4e1b-9bff-6b6ac2be0b85"}